                                                                                                                                    Bharti Airtel net rises 42%

     OUR BUREAU
                    
	New Delhi, Jan. 30: Bharti Airtel has reported a 42 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 1,722 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2007, against Rs 1,215 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. 
    
	The companys consolidated revenues grew 42 per cent to Rs 6,964 crore during the quarter from Rs 4,913 crore in the same period last year. 
    
	Chairman Sunil Mittal said the growth momentum would continue and the company would maintain its lead in a market that is becoming increasingly competitive as new players muscle in. With aggressive expansion plans, particularly in rural India, we are in a strong position, Mittal said in a statement.
    
	The government today allocated additional spectrum to Bharti Airtel in five telecom circles of Bengal, Gujarat, Uttar Pradesh (west), Assam and Haryana.
    
	The GSM mobile operator will get 6.2MHz of additional radiowaves for Bengal and 7.2MHz for the other four circles.
    
	The company had applied for additional spectrum in 10 telecom circles. 
    
	The other circles where the company is still awaiting spectrum are Rajasthan, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Bihar and Tamil Nadu. 
    
	Bharti expects to get additional spectrum in the rest of the circles in a couple of months.
    
	DLF profit up
    
	DLF has posted a 6 per cent increase in net profit for the third quarter ended December 31, 2007, at Rs 2,139 crore compared with Rs 2,018 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.
    
	The consolidated revenue was up 9 per cent to Rs 3,651 crore against Rs 3,349 crore in the year-ago period. 
    
	The profit for this quarter is about 10 per cent more than the entire profit of the last fiscal, primarily because of the execution of more projects, said Rajiv Singh, vice-chairman of DLF.
    
	M amp;M net jumps
    
	Mahindra amp; Mahindra has registered 68 per cent growth in net profit for the quarter ended December 31, 2007, at Rs 405.2 crore against Rs 241.7 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Gross revenues and other income for the third quarter rose 14.6 per cent to Rs 3,371.1 crore from Rs 2,942.8 crore a year ago. 
                                                                
